WEBVTT

00:04.258 --> 00:05.440
Welcome to Gospel in Life.

00:06.101 --> 00:13.773
In his first letter to early Christians, Peter tells believers they must grow up in their salvation, much like children maturing into adulthood.

00:14.233 --> 00:17.418
But what does it really look like to grow in our faith?

00:17.438 --> 00:27.474
Today, Tim Keller invites us to consider the lifelong journey of maturing spiritually and how we move toward a life that's deeply rooted in the redeeming work of Jesus Christ.

00:27.810 --> 00:33.377
After you listen, we invite you to go online to gospelandlife.com and sign up for our email updates.

00:33.857 --> 00:41.106
When you sign up, you'll receive our quarterly journal with stories of gospel changed lives, as well as other valuable gospel-centered resources.

00:41.527 --> 00:43.810
Subscribe today at gospelandlife.com.

00:44.370 --> 00:46.593
Now, here's Tim Keller with today's teaching.

00:54.163 --> 00:56.946
I'm going to read from 1 Peter chapter 1,

00:57.026 --> 00:58.888
Verse 22, over to chapter 2, verse 3.

00:58.908 --> 01:00.831
This is the third week in a row.

01:00.851 --> 01:02.072
We're looking at this passage.

01:02.933 --> 01:03.614
It's a rich one.

01:03.634 --> 01:11.023
1 Peter 1, 22, to chapter 2, verse 3, and it's printed, of course, in your bulletins.

01:11.784 --> 01:12.505
Let's look at it.

01:16.991 --> 01:26.162
Now that you have purified yourselves by obeying the truth, so that you have sincere love for your brothers, love one another deeply,

01:26.434 --> 01:27.015
from the heart.

01:27.996 --> 01:34.142
For you have been born again, not of perishable seed, but of imperishable, through the living and enduring word of God.

01:35.083 --> 01:39.709
For all men are like grass, and all their glory is like the flowers of the field.

01:40.029 --> 01:43.613
The grass withers and the flowers fall, but the word of the Lord stands forever.

01:44.053 --> 01:45.795
And this is the word that was preached to you.

01:47.197 --> 01:55.666
Therefore, rid yourselves of all malice and all deceit, hypocrisy, envy, and slander of every kind, like newborn babies,

01:56.482 --> 02:01.329
crave the pure spiritual milk so that by it you may grow up into your salvation.

02:01.989 --> 02:04.673
Now that you have tasted that the Lord is good.

02:06.015 --> 02:06.856
This is God's word.

02:06.876 --> 02:15.508
Now, I really want to just tonight home in on one phrase.

02:16.689 --> 02:21.476
I don't want to take any time to look at the structure.

02:22.017 --> 02:23.058
This passage

02:23.778 --> 02:27.744
tells us a great deal about how you can grow as a Christian.

02:29.726 --> 02:34.613
And the how-tos are here, and I'm going to ignore them for one more week and get into them next week.

02:35.254 --> 02:47.551
How can you, starting out as a new Christian, a spiritual baby, as it says here in verse 2, like a newborn babe, how can you grow up in your salvation?

02:48.412 --> 02:49.814
Grow up in your salvation.

02:50.595 --> 02:52.498
How can you do it?

02:53.698 --> 02:55.420
This passage tells us a great deal about it.

02:55.440 --> 02:59.063
There's three ways, and we're not going to look at any of them tonight.

03:01.446 --> 03:03.027
But you might want to write them down anyway.

03:04.889 --> 03:07.472
Years ago, I heard a lecture by J.I.

03:07.532 --> 03:18.182
Packer years ago in New England, and he looked at this passage, and he says, there's three ways to grow up into your salvation, and they're right here.

03:18.202 --> 03:22.226
He called them the way of nourishment, the way of acceptance,

03:22.402 --> 03:23.744
and the way of exchange.

03:24.265 --> 03:34.160
The way of nourishment, crave the spiritual milk, the word of God, the way of acceptance, purify yourself through obedience to the truth, and the way of exchange.

03:34.540 --> 03:36.203
Love one another sincerely and deeply.

03:36.704 --> 03:38.707
And we'll look at that next week, frankly.

03:39.288 --> 03:42.012
And here's what I want to look at tonight.

03:42.252 --> 03:51.346
I would like to look strictly at the very fact of this passage, this verse two, where it says,

03:51.778 --> 03:54.162
like newborn babies grow up.

03:55.483 --> 03:57.767
That's what it's saying, like newborn babies grow up.

03:58.388 --> 03:59.329
What does that mean?

03:59.369 --> 04:08.082
Before we talk about how to do it, I'm afraid if I jump right into it, Christians are real great, I mean, you know, American people are very practical.

04:08.342 --> 04:09.664
We're actually worse than that.

04:09.684 --> 04:10.445
We're pragmatic.

04:11.026 --> 04:13.089
We want to know the bottom line, how to do things.

04:13.129 --> 04:14.892
We want to know techniques.

04:15.613 --> 04:19.799
And before we run the techniques, we have to see what the heck it is that we're trying to accomplish.

04:20.560 --> 04:21.682
What does it mean?

04:21.794 --> 04:26.599
As newborn babies grow up, what does that mean?

04:27.320 --> 04:32.787
And all I want to do tonight is just reflect on that and ask ourselves, what does that mean?

04:33.027 --> 04:34.989
The Bible talks about this a number of places.

04:36.751 --> 04:49.906
Over in Hebrews, it talks about the fact that the writer of the Hebrews is referring to people who should by now be eating meat, but they still need milk.

04:50.338 --> 04:51.640
And there's another metaphor.

04:52.200 --> 05:06.957
The idea is that there is a kind of maturation process spiritually that parallels the biological and the mental and the psychological maturation process that we go through.

05:07.899 --> 05:17.650
It says in John, first John, there's a fascinating passage, chapter two, verse 11 and 12, where John says, I write to you little children,

05:17.986 --> 05:19.228
because your sins are forgiven.

05:19.828 --> 05:23.734
I write to you, fathers, because you have known Him who is from the beginning.

05:24.295 --> 05:30.683
And I write to you, young men, because you are strong, you have overcome the evil one, and the word of God abides in you.

05:31.124 --> 05:32.065
What is He talking about?

05:32.466 --> 05:47.666
And most writers understand that what John is saying is that there are different stages to the Christian life, just like there's different stages to the biological life, that there is babies, and then there's young men and women, in a sense, then there's fathers and mothers.

05:48.674 --> 05:56.593
and that, therefore, the Christian life must be seen as a process, a journey, a maturation process.

05:57.836 --> 06:03.730
We should all recognize, number one, that we are newborn babes when you become a Christian, and number two, we've got to grow up.

06:04.066 --> 06:05.128
Now, what does that mean?

06:05.168 --> 06:06.850
Let's just reflect on it.

06:06.870 --> 06:07.571
What does it mean?

06:08.032 --> 06:09.474
Next week, we can talk about how we do it.

06:09.494 --> 06:12.038
But what does it mean that we're new board names and grow up?

06:12.098 --> 06:13.140
First, let's look at the grow up.

06:13.580 --> 06:18.367
Then we'll look for a minute at what it means when the Bible tells us that when you become a Christian, you're a baby.

06:20.030 --> 06:21.091
We're learning two things here.

06:21.152 --> 06:23.115
We have to grow up and we're babies.

06:24.196 --> 06:25.178
Let's look at the grow up part.

06:25.318 --> 06:31.187
First, this is teaching that you must learn to think of Christianity in terms of growth stages.

06:32.228 --> 06:33.490
There are various stages.

06:33.762 --> 06:43.472
John, as we just mentioned, in a very parallel passage, just like Peter is saying, love one another, and then talks about the fact that you're a newborn baby and you need to grow in grace.

06:44.453 --> 06:48.658
So John, in 1 John, chapter 2, verse 11 and 12, says the same thing.

06:49.259 --> 06:55.445
He says, love one another, and then he says, I write to you children, I write to you young men, I write to you fathers.

06:55.766 --> 07:03.634
And he shows that he recognizes that inside the church that he's talking to, you have got these stages of Christian growth.

07:04.194 --> 07:22.094
To remember that, to realize that is very important, you must realize that you are on a spiritual journey very much like the journey that many of us have gone through of moving from babies and children to adolescents to grown adults.

07:22.114 --> 07:22.915
Isn't that frightening?

07:24.316 --> 07:26.258
To think that we have to do it again.

07:27.680 --> 07:31.544
And actually that is both the glory and the frightening part of Christianity.

07:32.105 --> 07:33.106
We're on a journey.

07:33.218 --> 07:34.200
It's a glorious thing.

07:35.182 --> 07:50.194
If you could imagine, if you had to actually, in the pioneer days, traverse the continent, if you got on a wagon and you had to traverse the continent of America, depending on where you were, at different stages in the trip.

07:50.466 --> 07:53.068
with different stages in the trip would require different skills.

07:53.249 --> 08:01.156
At some point you'd have to have the skills for how to deal with swamps and marshes and how to deal with heat.

08:01.496 --> 08:05.840
Other times you'd have to have skills to deal with climbing mountains and dealing with cold.

08:06.261 --> 08:17.672
By the time you got all the way to the end, having gone through every one of the stages, you would have learned this sort of skill set and this sort of skill set and this sort of skill set and by the end you'd be complete and ready for anything.

08:18.813 --> 08:20.274
And the Bible insists

08:20.962 --> 08:42.155
When John says, I write to you children, I write to you young men, I write to you fathers, what he's saying is that at every stage there are certain skills, there are certain lessons, there are certain attitudes, there are certain capacities, there are certain aptitudes that you will have to learn to master that stage and to move to the next one.

08:42.756 --> 08:44.338
That's fascinating, is it not?

08:44.578 --> 08:46.801
Christianity is not a static thing at all.

08:47.242 --> 08:49.224
It's not just getting into a status.

08:49.264 --> 08:50.145
It's not like nighthood.

08:50.165 --> 08:52.108
I've been knighted and now I go around.

08:52.428 --> 08:53.230
I am a knight.

08:53.430 --> 08:54.391
I've become a Christian.

08:54.411 --> 08:54.952
I'm a Christian.

08:55.252 --> 08:57.215
Instead, of course, it's this great journey.

08:57.896 --> 08:58.937
And that's the glory of it.

09:00.079 --> 09:02.262
But it's also very frightening.

09:04.144 --> 09:09.712
Children and youth don't understand themselves.

09:10.593 --> 09:14.578
You know, if you, most places in the world, the civilized world,

09:14.690 --> 09:28.954
Certainly every state of this union, certainly every place in America, if children and youth are allowed to do whatever they want, if there are no limits put on them by their parents or guardians or someone, if there's no guidance given, it's illegal.

09:29.134 --> 09:29.815
It's against the law.

09:29.835 --> 09:30.917
It's called child neglect.

09:31.979 --> 09:35.905
To not ever put any limits on your kids is child neglect.

09:35.965 --> 09:36.206
Why?

09:36.526 --> 09:38.930
Because kids are dumb.

09:39.810 --> 09:41.953
They don't understand their own feelings.

09:42.374 --> 09:44.257
They don't understand their own desires.

09:44.277 --> 09:46.039
They don't understand what's going on inside them.

09:46.059 --> 09:47.441
Let me give you a couple of examples.

09:49.424 --> 10:02.023
I noticed when I walk to our office, which is between 40th and 39th in Madison, and I walk down 40th Street from the subway station, there's ads, you know, of course, on the sides and the back of the telephone booths, which are fascinating.

10:02.163 --> 10:02.924
Great ads, too.

10:03.385 --> 10:09.554
There's one, just before I hit Madison Avenue, is a picture of a young

10:09.794 --> 10:17.905
woman, obviously a very young woman who's just hitting puberty with a vengeance, evidently, if you look at it.

10:18.365 --> 10:28.419
And she's looking in the mirror, and the heading says, welcome to your 15-year-old body, instructions to follow.

10:29.860 --> 10:37.170
And then your eyes go down the ad a little bit, and you suddenly realize that according to the ad, the instruction book is 17 magazine.

10:37.922 --> 10:54.883
Now, you can tell that this ad must be trying to get 15-year-old girls, for what I can tell, to read it, because no one who is an adult, no one with an ounce of sense would believe that 17 magazine are sufficient instructions to your 15-year-old body.

10:54.903 --> 10:56.685
I mean, nobody else is going to believe that.

10:56.725 --> 10:58.467
Nobody else is stupid enough to believe the ad.

10:59.208 --> 11:06.196
But the person who they're trying to get to buy in the magazine, welcome to your 15-year-old body.

11:06.256 --> 11:07.698
Now, what's behind that?

11:08.994 --> 11:13.819
When your body starts to develop and you start to have all these feelings, you have no idea what's going on.

11:13.859 --> 11:14.880
You don't understand them.

11:14.900 --> 11:15.921
You can't control them.

11:16.301 --> 11:17.402
You don't know what to do with them.

11:17.422 --> 11:19.484
You don't know how much to let them out and how much to keep them in.

11:19.544 --> 11:26.571
Well, what do you think the Bible means when it talks about growing up in your salvation?

11:27.892 --> 11:33.938
If you're a child, if you start out as a newborn baby and then you sort of move up spiritually, you're in the same situation.

11:34.158 --> 11:35.219
You are in the same boat.

11:35.500 --> 11:38.002
There's all kinds of things going on in you.

11:38.306 --> 11:42.092
that you don't understand, and you desperately need help.

11:42.853 --> 11:47.420
You need guidance as desperately as a child needs it, as desperately as a youth needed.

11:47.460 --> 11:48.582
You need instructions.

11:50.124 --> 11:51.065
Do you understand that?

11:51.927 --> 11:53.168
Let me give you a couple of examples.

11:53.850 --> 11:57.836
When you become a Christian, big change happens on the inside.

11:59.298 --> 12:06.068
Christians are people, Paul says, in whom the spirit warth against the flesh, and the flesh warth against the spirit.

12:06.409 --> 12:07.410
Now, many people

12:07.554 --> 12:11.000
In fact, most people have made a terrible and profound mistake.

12:11.701 --> 12:23.282
They believe that when Paul talks about the flesh, that Paul's talking about the desires of the body, like the desires for food, the desire for sex, and, you know, comforts, you know, physical comforts.

12:23.458 --> 12:30.208
And people think when Paul says the flesh worth against the spirit, that what Christians are supposed to do is they're supposed to beat down their bodily desires.

12:30.448 --> 12:41.604
They're not supposed to have sex, they're not supposed to eat nice things, they're not supposed to have physical comforts, they're supposed to in an ascetic kind of monastic way, pummel those desires and keep them down.

12:41.644 --> 12:43.286
That's not what Paul's talking about at all.

12:43.366 --> 12:44.568
Here's what Paul's talking about.

12:45.970 --> 12:51.698
Before you become a Christian, your heart is completely united in its opposition

12:52.450 --> 12:54.052
to God's salvation.

12:55.414 --> 13:01.482
Now, let me say this, it's gonna take a minute or two to say this, and you may have heard this before, but this is critical.

13:03.165 --> 13:09.433
Whether you're religious or you're religious, before you become a Christian, you are doing everything you can.

13:09.493 --> 13:17.464
Every part of your body, every part of your soul, your whole heart is united in absolute opposition to God as savior.

13:17.985 --> 13:19.487
You want to be your own savior.

13:19.707 --> 13:21.650
That's the one thing, your whole heart knows that.

13:21.794 --> 13:22.875
Your whole heart wants that.

13:23.436 --> 13:28.121
Now some people try self-salvation through morality and religion.

13:28.561 --> 13:32.846
Other people try self-salvation through immorality and religion.

13:33.867 --> 13:35.008
It makes no difference.

13:36.229 --> 13:46.580
In both cases, here's the person who's smug and self-righteous and a person who's sure that God will love and receive them into heaven because they go to church and they are good and they do.

13:46.941 --> 13:48.242
They're good Christian people.

13:48.482 --> 14:02.998
And over here are people who are doing their very best through the seeking of power and of pleasure, through maybe even violence and through a licentious lifestyle to fulfill themselves and find themselves in the way of the French existentialists.

14:03.238 --> 14:04.139
They try everything.

14:04.419 --> 14:06.021
You look at them and they seem so opposite.

14:06.301 --> 14:09.925
The Bible says they're absolutely the same, spiritually.

14:10.766 --> 14:14.930
Each one of them, in very radically different ways, is after the same thing.

14:15.151 --> 14:18.354
They're trying to avoid a Savior.

14:18.850 --> 14:26.083
moral people, religious people are doing everything they can to be as good as possible, to be as decent as possible, so they don't need a Savior.

14:26.704 --> 14:28.608
Oh, they, you know, they think they need a Savior.

14:28.628 --> 14:37.163
They say they believe in a Savior, but frankly, the whole purpose of their religion, until you become a Christian, the purpose of your religion is to avoid needing a real Savior.

14:37.223 --> 14:38.065
You're your own Savior.

14:39.968 --> 14:43.154
And there's really no difference between the religious person, the irreligious person,

14:43.330 --> 14:46.815
One thing is true of everybody in the world before they become Christians.

14:46.875 --> 14:47.977
They are united.

14:48.017 --> 14:52.985
Their whole hearts are united in opposition to the idea of needing a Savior.

14:53.606 --> 14:57.552
See, the Bible does not divide the world the way most people do into good and bad people.

14:58.213 --> 14:58.393
No.

14:58.954 --> 15:04.802
The Bible says there's good people and there's bad people who don't want a Savior, and then there's the people who do.

15:05.423 --> 15:07.867
Those are the two groups of people in the whole world.

15:08.107 --> 15:12.434
Those who are sure they don't need a Savior, those who do not want a Savior, and those who do.

15:14.338 --> 15:22.354
And when you become a Christian, the mommy you become a Christian into your life comes a new system, a new power.

15:23.597 --> 15:35.922
And your heart begins to operate on a whole new system of identity, a whole new system of morality, a whole new system of life.

15:36.386 --> 15:51.053
in which you say, the reason that I have self-worth, the reason that I know who I am, the reason I have happiness, the basis of my identity is the fact that Jesus died for me, that his righteousness has been transferred to my account.

15:52.515 --> 15:53.678
And that's the new system.

15:53.858 --> 16:00.530
And yet the Bible says, you still got a major part of your heart that still wants to operate on the old system.

16:01.954 --> 16:08.123
And so before you become a Christian, your heart is united in one system, self-salvation.

16:08.864 --> 16:16.495
And now when you become a Christian, your heart has two different vying systems at each other, trying to get control.

16:16.876 --> 16:20.621
The one that says Christ is my Savior, and the other one that says something else.

16:21.743 --> 16:22.784
I want something else to be.

16:24.206 --> 16:29.714
Now what this means is actually that the part of your heart that was

16:30.306 --> 16:43.080
You know, against God, the part of your heart that wanted self-salvation, the part of your heart that Paul calls the flesh, before you became a Christian, that part of your heart was in charge.

16:43.721 --> 16:46.824
Now, we all know what happens if you corner a bear.

16:46.884 --> 16:53.191
People, park rangers will always tell you that a bear is not dangerous unless it feels cornered.

16:54.653 --> 16:59.378
And, of course, a bear gets very, very dangerous if you shoot it in the leg.

17:00.002 --> 17:02.945
You don't expect a bear, then, to come and eat out of your hand.

17:03.326 --> 17:04.627
You expect a bear to attack you.

17:05.067 --> 17:11.454
When you become a Christian, one of the things that, you know, into your life comes the Holy Spirit.

17:11.535 --> 17:16.220
Into your life comes this new power, and it deals a mortal death blow to the flesh.

17:17.101 --> 17:19.683
It deals a mortal death blow to that old system.

17:20.324 --> 17:24.809
It comes right into the face of the old system and throws it off the throne of the heart.

17:24.829 --> 17:25.810
What happens to it?

17:26.658 --> 17:39.382
That part of your life, your pride, your selfishness, your fears, your defensiveness, your self-consciousness, it's cornered, it's wounded, and now it's far more aggravated and far more ferocious than it ever was before.

17:39.843 --> 17:49.682
And so very often what happens is after you become a Christian, you may find, in fact, at some point you will find that after all the great loving feelings wear off,

17:50.050 --> 17:53.535
You may find thoughts coming into your heart and you may find temptations coming to you.

17:53.555 --> 18:00.244
And you may find your ideas and concepts and desires coming out of your heart far worse than anything you'd ever seen before.

18:00.565 --> 18:01.946
And you're absolutely upset.

18:02.347 --> 18:03.228
You can't understand it.

18:03.248 --> 18:04.290
I gave my life to Christ.

18:04.730 --> 18:05.692
Didn't the Holy Spirit come in?

18:06.012 --> 18:07.094
What is going on here?

18:07.134 --> 18:07.995
What is going on here?

18:09.096 --> 18:10.639
Welcome to your 15-year-old body.

18:15.525 --> 18:16.807
Instructions to follow.

18:16.847 --> 18:18.930
You are a kid.

18:20.930 --> 18:25.516
You see, by the way, is there anything that I just said that's news to any of you?

18:26.637 --> 18:35.729
I said that a Christian who's mature expects the sinful part of their heart to be worse after conversion than it was before.

18:35.829 --> 18:39.113
More aggravated, more ferocious, more upset, in a corner.

18:41.516 --> 18:42.317
Does that surprise you?

18:42.338 --> 18:44.080
I hear our babes.

18:44.861 --> 18:45.842
That's okay.

18:46.018 --> 18:47.580
Everybody starts out that way.

18:47.841 --> 18:49.363
What do babies know about themselves?

18:49.543 --> 18:50.865
They don't even remember their birth.

18:51.226 --> 18:51.887
They don't know much.

18:54.350 --> 18:59.558
There's the frightening part of what the Bible is teaching here.

19:00.199 --> 19:03.965
When you become a Christian, all kinds of things begin to happen to you.

19:04.305 --> 19:05.287
All sorts of new things.

19:05.487 --> 19:06.308
You don't understand them.

19:06.328 --> 19:07.851
You don't understand what's going on inside you.

19:07.871 --> 19:09.052
You don't understand the world around you.

19:09.373 --> 19:10.194
You need help.

19:10.722 --> 19:13.473
You need to depend on other people, people who are further down the line.

19:13.493 --> 19:14.737
You need to go to the Word of God.

19:14.778 --> 19:15.440
You need the church.

19:15.460 --> 19:16.223
You need these things.

19:16.725 --> 19:22.226
Don't you dare think that you can be self-contained little units.

19:23.170 --> 19:25.633
In other words, I'm a Christian, and I just move around.

19:25.653 --> 19:28.237
I like this church, I like that church, I like this teacher, I like that teacher.

19:28.257 --> 19:29.739
I like these Christians, I don't like these Christians.

19:30.039 --> 19:37.430
And so, you know, it's like going through a cafeteria, like a little bit of this, a little bit of that, as if you're in totally in charge of your life, you're totally in charge of your growth.

19:37.630 --> 19:38.551
That's impossible.

19:38.952 --> 19:52.370
And if you really think that you can move ahead like that in the Christian life without submitting to wiser heads, without really coming in and saying, I'm a babe, you've got to help me.

19:52.866 --> 19:54.168
You're gonna make a shipwreck of things.

19:54.869 --> 20:01.658
You'll be just as, what kind of life are homeless kids gonna have wandering around on the streets?

20:01.958 --> 20:03.120
What kind of life are they gonna have?

20:04.221 --> 20:05.082
You're in the same boat.

20:06.144 --> 20:06.705
You're babes.

20:08.026 --> 20:09.208
We all start out that way.

20:09.889 --> 20:12.132
We don't like it, but that's the way it is.

20:13.374 --> 20:17.159
Now, having said that, you see, I'm just trying to get it across.

20:17.419 --> 20:21.545
This, when it says, like newborn babies, crave the pure spiritual milk.

20:21.565 --> 20:22.546
It sounds so,

20:22.626 --> 20:25.570
sweet, so cute, so warm, and so soft.

20:25.750 --> 20:27.933
Ivory soap, you know, just sounds wonderful.

20:28.374 --> 20:29.475
But it's an insult.

20:30.216 --> 20:30.757
Wake up.

20:31.458 --> 20:32.419
You are babies.

20:33.321 --> 20:34.983
You do not understand what's going on.

20:35.403 --> 20:37.046
You don't understand your own selves.

20:37.887 --> 20:39.369
You've got to be parented.

20:39.409 --> 20:46.098
Now I know plenty of churches who have really abused this very thing.

20:46.978 --> 20:51.984
Plenty of churches have come in and groups have come in authoritarian, cultic.

20:52.365 --> 20:54.527
They've come in and said, ah, you're a new convert.

20:54.547 --> 20:55.809
Do everything we tell you.

20:56.209 --> 20:58.813
And you know there's groups like that in New York, of course.

20:59.193 --> 21:00.355
There's groups like that everywhere.

21:00.935 --> 21:03.098
And I know that can be abused, absolutely.

21:03.118 --> 21:06.622
And there's all sorts of qualifications you have to make to this and so forth.

21:06.923 --> 21:09.086
But I don't think that I should have to deal with that tonight.

21:09.106 --> 21:12.690
I think, generally speaking, the problem that Christians have is the opposite extreme.

21:13.346 --> 21:26.245
I know there's Christians that are so insecure, so marginalized, so desperately want authority in their lives and want approval in their lives that they're very happy to come and put themselves in under cultic authoritarian leadership, who tell them things like this.

21:26.766 --> 21:28.308
But that doesn't mean that this isn't true.

21:28.348 --> 21:30.712
And that doesn't mean that a lot of you don't need to hear it.

21:31.052 --> 21:31.693
You're babes.

21:31.814 --> 21:33.556
You have got to get advice.

21:33.917 --> 21:35.299
You need the instructions.

21:37.222 --> 21:37.522
Let's see.

21:38.114 --> 21:43.662
You don't understand your 15-year-old body spiritually anymore than you understood your 15-year-old body biologically.

21:43.983 --> 21:45.065
Isn't that a frightening thought?

21:45.365 --> 21:48.350
Think about what fools you were when you were 15.

21:48.830 --> 21:49.531
Think about it.

21:49.551 --> 21:59.466
Think about the mistakes you made and realize how much more help you had from people who were biologically and psychologically mature.

21:59.887 --> 22:01.890
You had teachers, you had parents, things like that.

22:02.591 --> 22:03.833
What's going on with you now?

22:03.873 --> 22:07.058
Have you got the kind of help that will enable you to spiritually mature?

22:08.738 --> 22:09.780
Are you willing to see that?

22:11.543 --> 22:12.664
Okay, let me move on.

22:13.225 --> 22:14.427
What are these growth stages?

22:14.588 --> 22:16.591
Okay, I'm telling you that there are stages of growth.

22:16.611 --> 22:17.072
What are they?

22:17.613 --> 22:19.075
Let me suggest something to you.

22:19.476 --> 22:28.811
I'd cross reference over to 1 John chapter 2 where he says, and I'll read it again, I write to you little children because your sins are forgiven.

22:29.512 --> 22:33.138
I write to you fathers because you know him who is from the beginning.

22:33.474 --> 22:40.102
And I write to you, young men, because you are strong, you have overcome the wicked one, and the word of God abideth in you.

22:40.924 --> 22:48.854
Now, a man named John Newton, the guy who wrote Amazing Grace and a lot of other great hymns, once wrote, he was a letter writer.

22:49.294 --> 22:51.056
In fact, I don't know.

22:51.076 --> 22:52.779
Do we have his letters on our book table?

22:53.299 --> 22:53.880
David Dewey?

22:54.901 --> 22:56.043
Probably sold out pretty soon.

22:56.063 --> 22:57.405
Can I have any now?

22:58.065 --> 22:58.546
Anyway.

22:58.786 --> 23:05.673
If you get his little book, well, he's written a lot of letters, but there's a little paperback edition called The Letters of John Newton.

23:05.693 --> 23:11.658
And the first three letters in that book are called Grace in the Blade, Grace in the Ear, and Grace in the Foolier of Corn.

23:11.999 --> 23:25.191
And he believes that there's basically three stages to the Christian life, to Christian growth, that parallel, the three things, the three stages that John talks about in his first epistle of John.

23:25.792 --> 23:27.954
And on the basis of what John Newton says,

23:28.546 --> 23:34.554
Let me just give you a kind of general broad brush outline of those three stages.

23:37.097 --> 23:40.381
Jesus was the most influential man to ever walk the earth.

23:40.982 --> 23:45.828
And his story has been told through books, movies, and articles in hundreds of different ways.

23:46.369 --> 23:47.931
Can anything more be said about him?

23:48.692 --> 23:56.562
In his book, Jesus the King, Tim Keller journeys through the gospel of Mark to reveal how the life of Jesus helps us make sense of our lives.

23:56.898 --> 24:05.851
Dr. Keller shows us how the story of Jesus is at once cosmic, historical, and personal, calling each of us to take a fresh look at our relationship with God.

24:06.612 --> 24:16.466
During the month of March, we'll send you a copy of Jesus the King as our thanks for your gift to help gospel and life share the transforming love of Christ with people all over the world.

24:16.834 --> 24:20.103
So request your copy today at gospelandlife.com.

24:20.424 --> 24:22.831
That's gospelandlife.com.

24:23.172 --> 24:26.962
Now here's Dr. Keller with the remainder of today's teaching.

24:29.858 --> 24:37.926
I want to start by saying, do not think that I am teaching you that there's only three stages and that everybody goes through these stages in this way.

24:38.326 --> 24:55.742
When the Bible gives illustrations like this, I write to you children, I write to you young men, I write to you fathers, I don't think in a case like that that John, the Gospel writer John is trying to say, there's only three stages and that everybody crosses over the line at a certain definable spot.

24:55.843 --> 24:57.684
I don't believe that at all, not for a minute.

24:58.805 --> 24:59.506
And yet,

24:59.714 --> 25:09.345
It'll help you start thinking in the right directions if I show you what John Newton says and what the gospel writer John says, or in the first epistle, these three stages are.

25:09.385 --> 25:16.493
And I think, as a pastor, having worked for almost 20 years in this business of watching people grow, I think there's a lot of truth to it.

25:16.694 --> 25:17.234
Here, listen.

25:18.596 --> 25:19.757
Like newborn babes grow up.

25:19.797 --> 25:20.338
How do you grow up?

25:20.939 --> 25:21.880
Think of these three stages.

25:21.940 --> 25:27.346
First of all, John says, I write to you children because you know your sins are forgiven.

25:30.370 --> 25:47.781
I think that the reason he says babies, children, in the first stage, you have to know your sins are forgiven, is that this is the very first lesson to know that your sins are forgiven, and you will never get out of spiritual babyhood until you do learn it.

25:48.663 --> 25:55.154
And many of us, and many of you, have been in spiritual babyhood for years because you don't know it yet.

25:55.970 --> 25:58.153
This is the first lesson you've got to get down.

25:58.213 --> 26:02.758
At every stage, there's a sort of lesson, I think, that has to get down before you can move on.

26:03.599 --> 26:04.540
And that's the first lesson.

26:04.560 --> 26:05.922
Do you know that your sins are forgiven?

26:05.962 --> 26:09.886
Now, a lot of you are saying, that's an awfully easy lesson.

26:09.906 --> 26:11.648
Everybody knows that God forgives sins.

26:11.708 --> 26:12.670
Jesus died on the cross.

26:13.070 --> 26:13.310
No.

26:14.512 --> 26:15.553
No, you don't.

26:17.836 --> 26:19.858
John Newton says,

26:20.386 --> 26:28.176
that the child in Christ, the baby, the baby Christian is somebody who has, quote, the remnants of a legalistic spirit.

26:29.678 --> 26:31.860
He says, you know that you're still a baby in Christ.

26:32.081 --> 26:32.701
Let me read this.

26:33.122 --> 26:39.069
Because he or she still tends to be overly sensitive to criticism, finds repentance difficult and galling.

26:39.690 --> 26:42.494
It's still fairly insecure in how he or she is being perceived.

26:42.574 --> 26:42.874
Why?

26:43.415 --> 26:46.098
Because they do not know that they're forgiven and loved.

26:46.658 --> 26:51.786
They do not know they're forgiven and accepted, and there's still lots of works righteousness clinging to them.

26:53.489 --> 26:54.230
Do you know what that's saying?

26:55.553 --> 27:00.721
Why do you think a person says, well, I know that my sins are forgiven, but you don't.

27:02.244 --> 27:11.058
There's plenty of people who stay in spiritual babiness, because even though they say intellectually, I know, but I'm accepted in Jesus Christ, they don't really understand that.

27:11.490 --> 27:15.174
Why does John Newton say works righteousness is still clinging to you?

27:15.194 --> 27:20.520
Well, for example, many of you are still very, very sensitive to criticism.

27:21.621 --> 27:30.872
Many of you are still extremely up and down, depending on emotionally, depending on whether people are liking you and approving of you and noticing you or not.

27:32.333 --> 27:35.857
Some of you are extremely up and down, depending on how your careers are going.

27:36.698 --> 27:39.321
And so emotionally, you're really up and down and up and down.

27:39.701 --> 27:40.242
Why?

27:40.994 --> 27:42.436
You don't know that your sins are forgiven.

27:43.057 --> 27:47.042
John Newton would say, you still, remember, there's two systems now.

27:47.202 --> 27:52.288
There's the system of self-salvation and there's the system of Christ as your savior.

27:52.569 --> 28:06.126
And you, baby Christians are people who though they intellectually believe that Christ is their savior, actually and psychologically and functionally, in their day-to-day life, they act as if something else is their savior.

28:07.187 --> 28:09.490
And so radically, they're still insecure.

28:09.890 --> 28:12.193
They still really don't believe that Jesus loves them.

28:12.514 --> 28:14.196
They still don't really believe that they're forgiven.

28:14.236 --> 28:17.661
They still really, in a sense, are still trying to earn that forgiveness.

28:17.721 --> 28:20.124
And as long as you're in that state, you're still a baby.

28:20.144 --> 28:21.506
You'll never get out of babyhood.

28:22.688 --> 28:23.629
Let me put it to you this way.

28:24.510 --> 28:30.198
David Martin Lloyd-Jones wrote a sermon, preached a sermon years ago on this passage in 1 John.

28:30.679 --> 28:36.146
And he has a very interesting statement that I just lifted right out along the reader to you, quote,

28:36.802 --> 28:41.807
He says, let me put this in a practical form, and I do not hesitate to put it like this.

28:42.668 --> 28:47.692
If you are uncertain about the forgiveness of your sins, that in itself is a sin.

28:49.734 --> 28:53.838
If you are uncertain, by the way, some of you are definitely uncertain whether your sins are forgiven tonight.

28:53.998 --> 28:54.959
Now listen to what he says.

28:56.681 --> 28:58.723
This is a bullet between your eyes, I hope.

28:59.844 --> 29:02.786
Let me put it in this practical form, and I do not hesitate to put it like this.

29:02.887 --> 29:06.610
If you are uncertain about the forgiveness of your sins, that in itself is a sin.

29:07.330 --> 29:13.376
I want to be ruthless about this because there are many people who feel that an assurance of forgiveness of sins is presumption.

29:13.957 --> 29:16.579
And they rather give the impression that they are being humble and modest.

29:16.599 --> 29:19.562
They say, oh, I would not like to say my sins are forgiven.

29:19.842 --> 29:21.284
I do not feel good enough to say that.

29:21.324 --> 29:22.265
I am so unworthy."

29:23.066 --> 29:24.047
Do any of you talk like that?

29:24.487 --> 29:28.531
And he says, they give the impression that they have much loneliness and humility.

29:28.851 --> 29:35.698
The simple reply to that is this, if you do not know you have been forgiven, it is because you are still relying upon yourself.

29:36.898 --> 29:41.244
because you are not relying upon the finished and complete work of the Son of God for you on the cross.

29:41.725 --> 29:44.850
It's because you do not realize the merit and power of his blessed name.

29:45.571 --> 29:46.192
And he goes on.

29:47.293 --> 29:50.678
And he simply says this, tonight, do you know that your sins are forgiven?

29:50.698 --> 29:52.040
Are you absolutely sure?

29:52.080 --> 29:57.649
Are you sure that no matter what you've just done or what you're about to do or no matter what you do that your sins can't condemn you?

29:57.709 --> 30:00.473
Do you know that your sins are forgiven?

30:00.513 --> 30:03.618
Do you know that nothing can snatch you out of his hand?

30:03.678 --> 30:04.279
Do you know it?

30:05.480 --> 30:06.642
And he goes on and says,

30:07.010 --> 30:20.130
This is the first thing you can't get past this stage unless and until you become clear that Jesus Christ has borne your sins, has died your death, has risen again to stand as your representative, your surety, your advocate, your substitute before the Father.

30:20.170 --> 30:33.490
Do you utterly and absolutely rely upon Him and Him alone and nothing else for your standing before the throne of God if you do, and only if you do, you can say you know your sins are forgiven.

30:34.050 --> 30:36.955
I write to you children because you know your sins are forgiven.

30:37.556 --> 30:40.961
Until you know it, you'll never move on.

30:41.802 --> 30:46.390
I hope you see that a lot of you have stayed in spiritual babyhood for years because you don't know it.

30:47.371 --> 30:53.100
Because though intellectually you say, Jesus is my Savior, you're continually sliding back into other things that's just salvation.

30:53.120 --> 30:59.090
So you're always feeling so unworthy and you're always wondering whether God really loves you and whether he really has taken care of you.

30:59.458 --> 31:02.461
because you look at your failures and they just accuse you in your heart.

31:02.681 --> 31:04.243
You still don't understand the gospel.

31:04.283 --> 31:05.764
You still don't know your sins are forgiven.

31:06.004 --> 31:07.986
You'll never move beyond babyhood.

31:09.468 --> 31:09.708
Never.

31:11.430 --> 31:12.651
But then there's the second stage.

31:13.952 --> 31:21.379
He says, I write to you young men because you have overcome the evil one and you are strong and the word of God abideth in you.

31:21.540 --> 31:22.300
What's that stage?

31:22.460 --> 31:28.146
Now, John Newton believes that spiritual adolescence is a lot like

31:28.642 --> 31:34.851
regular adolescents, you know, when you have a little baby or a little kid, you never let the kid cross the street by him or herself.

31:35.893 --> 31:42.823
You never let the kid, you know, you don't say to a four-year-old now, honey, you know, go to nursery school, here's a subway token, you don't do that.

31:44.566 --> 31:49.373
You take them by the hand, and therefore, they always sense your presence.

31:50.795 --> 31:52.177
They always feel you right there.

31:53.239 --> 31:57.906
Your parents never let you miss a step or miss a beat.

31:58.562 --> 32:01.009
Now, you can't do that when the kid's 14.

32:02.073 --> 32:03.437
You can't do that when the kid's 24.

32:03.597 --> 32:05.684
You can't say, here, honey, I'll take you to school.

32:06.245 --> 32:10.418
At some point, you've got to let them cross the street without you.

32:11.426 --> 32:13.728
And John Newton draws an image from that.

32:13.828 --> 32:28.522
He says, listen, if we really believe the Bible is right in saying that the Bible is very clear in talking about physical and biological and psychological maturation as being parallel, he says, here's where you know you started to grow up and become at least, you've moved out of spiritual babyhood.

32:28.923 --> 32:36.790
When God starts to call you to face things without the sense of his presence and his love.

32:37.751 --> 32:40.594
In other words, sometimes the reason

32:41.410 --> 32:45.835
that you're finding that he doesn't seem to be very real, and yet you've got all these things you've got to do.

32:46.916 --> 32:54.144
And you say, if only I had the strength, if only I felt your presence, I know I'm supposed to do this, I know I'm supposed to do that, and yet, Lord, I just don't feel you there.

32:55.466 --> 32:58.730
John Newton says that's probably God saying it's time to cross the street by yourself.

33:00.532 --> 33:01.713
In fact, let me give you a quote.

33:01.953 --> 33:02.614
He says this.

33:03.395 --> 33:09.842
He says, stage A, babyhood, was marked by high feelings and little knowledge of the truth.

33:10.274 --> 33:15.581
Stage B is marked by lower feelings and growth in the knowledge of the truth.

33:16.482 --> 33:21.448
See, young men, you have overcome the evil one and the word of God abided the new.

33:21.869 --> 33:32.262
So John Newton goes along and says, this is how you know you've moved out of spiritual babyhood and you're moving into the next stage and you're really learning to be strong and have the word of God abide in you.

33:32.302 --> 33:34.965
He says, you will become more mistrustful of your own heart.

33:35.526 --> 33:38.770
You will see the dimensions and peculiar nature of your own sinful nature.

33:38.978 --> 33:40.380
You'll become more dependent on God.

33:40.400 --> 33:42.162
You'll finally learn how to cling to God in prayer.

33:42.182 --> 33:47.810
You will learn to go into the Word and to rely on it and make it your guide instead of feelings and impulses.

33:48.511 --> 33:52.657
You become more humble and loving and forgiving of others, and in the end, far more useful to God.

33:52.697 --> 33:58.245
In other words, John Newton says, the way you know that you've moved out of spiritual babyhood is that God is not always there.

33:59.166 --> 34:01.069
You don't always feel Him.

34:01.089 --> 34:04.914
Sometimes you have got to step out and go on the bare Word of God.

34:06.050 --> 34:19.929
Now, this is very traumatic, because I've often had people say, you know, when I first became a Christian, God always seemed so real to me, and every time I went to worship, I ended with tears in my eyes, and his love was always there, and he always felt he had me by the hand.

34:20.209 --> 34:23.634
And now, for some reason, you know, I don't always sense him.

34:23.694 --> 34:25.236
The quiet times aren't always good.

34:25.296 --> 34:27.499
He wants you to grow up.

34:28.921 --> 34:35.410
He wants you to do things not just because he's got you by the hand, but because you have begun to understand his mind.

34:36.066 --> 34:41.354
because you're beginning to rely on his word and not just simply on him picking you up and taking you places.

34:42.055 --> 34:44.078
I mean, I don't want that in my 14-year-old.

34:44.659 --> 34:46.342
I don't want that in a 24-year-old.

34:46.482 --> 34:56.477
I want enough of me to have come down into them so that they now are able to move about on their own and not need me to always be there, taking them everywhere, grabbing them, holding them by the hand.

34:56.777 --> 34:57.138
You see?

34:58.981 --> 35:00.082
In other words, let's put it this way.

35:01.224 --> 35:02.546
You never become.

35:04.290 --> 35:07.374
Spiritually, a young man or woman, strong.

35:09.617 --> 35:12.922
Spiritually becoming self-sufficient.

35:13.542 --> 35:21.112
Oh, it's very got to be very careful because you see, on the one hand, John Newton said, the mark of this second stage is that you're more dependent on God.

35:21.132 --> 35:24.297
Yes, dependent on God and not on your feelings about God.

35:25.679 --> 35:26.740
See, that's what's the problem.

35:26.840 --> 35:28.963
Babies always have got to have those great feelings.

35:29.484 --> 35:30.185
They've got to.

35:30.465 --> 35:32.267
They've always got to feel God's got them by the hand.

35:33.209 --> 35:34.290
And you'll stay a baby.

35:34.850 --> 35:37.734
You know, put it this way.

35:38.675 --> 35:49.768
If nobody gets out of childhood without figuring out the difference between grace and works, the difference between knowing that your sins are forgiven because of your salvation in Christ and your self-salvations.

35:50.409 --> 36:04.146
If you never get out of babyhood, unless you understand your sins are forgiven, you never get out of adolescence until you learn to say, everything is necessary that he sends and nothing can be necessary that he withholds.

36:06.466 --> 36:15.179
You never get out of spiritual adolescence until you start to realize, until you stop the self-pity and the temper tantrums of babies.

36:15.800 --> 36:16.741
You stop blubbering.

36:17.963 --> 36:24.893
You start to realize that life is tough and that you've got the word of God and you've got his promises and move out on that.

36:24.953 --> 36:28.899
And why do I always have to have these great feelings of power and great feelings of love?

36:29.620 --> 36:30.161
Do you see that?

36:30.601 --> 36:33.746
As John says, young men, you are strong.

36:34.146 --> 36:35.288
Learn to obey.

36:35.708 --> 36:36.670
Learn just to do it.

36:36.710 --> 36:38.092
Learn to go on the bare word of God.

36:38.132 --> 36:39.614
Learn to finally live by faith.

36:39.654 --> 36:43.760
That's the second stage.

36:44.020 --> 36:51.271
And in the third stage, fathers, it says, I write to you, fathers, because you have known Him who is from the beginning.

36:52.994 --> 36:59.543
Now see, in the end, I think the last stage, the advanced stage of Christianity is just this.

37:00.605 --> 37:01.426
They know Him.

37:02.114 --> 37:07.680
See, the ultimate advanced Christian is the person who really communes with God.

37:07.700 --> 37:13.026
Now, you know, when we were going through the book of Ephesians, we talked a great deal about this in the summertime.

37:13.486 --> 37:25.760
It says in Ephesians 1 and chapter 3, it says, I pray that the eyes of your heart would be enlightened, that you might be strengthened the inner being, that you can know the height and width and breadth and depth of the love of God, which surpasses knowledge, and be filled with all the fullness of God.

37:26.621 --> 37:31.346
You see, if you're a baby, or even if you're an adolescent,

37:31.842 --> 37:32.363
in Christ.

37:32.784 --> 37:52.722
You find that there is times in which because of troubles you go to God and you spend a lot of time in prayer and you spend a lot of time studying the Scripture and sometimes you have these periodic crises times in which God's love just floats down on you and you have this great experience of His presence

37:52.898 --> 38:00.068
and you actually feel that you know the height with the breath and the depth of the love of God, and you're filled with all the fullness of God, but they are sporadic.

38:00.108 --> 38:02.432
They're very rare, and they usually happen when you're having trouble.

38:04.514 --> 38:07.719
You only pray like your life depends on it when you're in trouble.

38:09.862 --> 38:15.470
And that's really when you have the best times of your life spiritually, and they're very sporadic.

38:15.510 --> 38:21.138
And most of us, if you've been a Christian for five years or more, you've had some of those experiences, but they are not normal.

38:21.410 --> 38:27.976
You have not learned the routine, you have not learned the discipline, and you have not learned the skills of regular communion with God.

38:29.258 --> 38:30.499
That's an advanced person.

38:31.780 --> 38:39.588
Somebody like Jacob, wrestling member with the angel, and he said, I will not let you go till you bless me.

38:41.750 --> 38:45.634
Someone like Moses who said to God, show me your glory.

38:46.094 --> 38:49.938
An advanced Christian doesn't just do that when the chips are down.

38:50.658 --> 39:01.960
A father or mother in the faith is someone who has learned through spending the time, through relentless passion, a deep yearning that's consistent.

39:02.621 --> 39:04.023
You finally started to penetrate.

39:04.384 --> 39:06.128
You have regular communion with him.

39:06.769 --> 39:08.592
You know the one that is from the beginning.

39:08.833 --> 39:09.554
And there we go.

39:09.826 --> 39:13.472
You put it this way, your babies, until you understand the difference in grace and works.

39:13.912 --> 39:18.699
You're out of lessons, so you understand that everything is necessary that he sends, nothing can be necessarily withholds.

39:19.040 --> 39:36.306
You stop blubbering about the hardness of life, you learn how to live according to the bare word of God, and lastly, you become a father or mother in the faith when you start to learn the disciplines of prayer and communing with him, so that you regularly are seeing his glory.

39:37.314 --> 39:41.961
You notice, by the way, I spent more time on children, a little less time on adolescence, and very little time on fathers and mothers.

39:41.981 --> 39:42.402
You know why?

39:42.442 --> 39:48.451
Because we have less and less data about each group.

39:48.471 --> 39:48.912
You know why?

39:48.952 --> 39:52.898
Because most Christians stay babies all their lives, and only very few even get out of that.

39:56.323 --> 39:57.405
Do you see where you are?

39:58.066 --> 39:59.348
Can you recognize yourself?

39:59.989 --> 40:03.915
I don't mean to give people the impressioners a nice, these are nice, clear-cut categories.

40:04.596 --> 40:06.098
But are you seeing progress?

40:07.746 --> 40:09.028
Or are you stuck right now?

40:09.789 --> 40:12.073
Because you haven't learned the lesson for your stage.

40:13.656 --> 40:19.626
Okay, lastly, now we've already seen, number one, that it's a frightening thing to be a child.

40:19.927 --> 40:22.231
To be a spiritual baby means that you need help.

40:23.052 --> 40:23.974
You've got to get help.

40:24.014 --> 40:25.216
You've got to submit to the help.

40:25.576 --> 40:28.141
You've got to see that you need other people to move you along.

40:29.243 --> 40:33.650
B, we've seen something about what it means to move along through this growth stages.

40:33.922 --> 40:38.507
We haven't talked about how that's next week, but we're talking about what it is and what you should be looking forward to.

40:38.547 --> 41:02.994
But lastly, let me just ask you and let me just make an urgent appeal to humble yourselves because we don't like to think of ourselves as babies, but let me tell you the sins of spiritual babiness so that you can see them and you can identify them and you can kind of repent of them, but with hope because you see, there's a kind of sin

41:03.074 --> 41:10.125
When I see a five-year-old acting in a way that's wrong, I have to say to him or her, don't do that.

41:10.345 --> 41:16.134
I have to correct him or her, but I also have a lot of hope because that's a five-year-old sin, and I know they're going to grow out of it.

41:16.855 --> 41:18.358
Just a couple of words here.

41:19.900 --> 41:31.378
You have to realize, and it's going to be galling to a lot of you in New York, that when you start as a Christian, you are a baby, no matter how smart you are naturally, no matter how talented you are naturally,

41:32.034 --> 41:38.763
You remember a couple years ago, I did some teaching on this, the Bible teaches that God gives good gifts to everybody.

41:39.144 --> 41:40.345
He gives common sense.

41:40.465 --> 41:41.547
He gives brilliance.

41:41.567 --> 41:42.969
He gives artistic talent.

41:43.429 --> 41:44.971
He gives plan IQ.

41:48.616 --> 41:49.838
He gives management skills.

41:49.878 --> 41:51.100
He gives these out to everybody.

41:51.821 --> 41:59.311
He just throws them out there in the world the way a gardener would sort of throw seeds out on a bank to, you know, flower seeds on a bank just to make it beautiful.

41:59.631 --> 42:01.714
He throws these things out.

42:01.890 --> 42:07.416
But some of you are very, very, very, very smart naturally.

42:07.476 --> 42:09.678
Some of you are tremendously talented naturally.

42:10.018 --> 42:13.482
And when you become a Christian, you start out as an infant.

42:14.643 --> 42:15.804
And that's a little hard for you.

42:17.185 --> 42:19.848
An awful lot of people over the years have come to Redeemer.

42:20.188 --> 42:20.849
And I can see it.

42:22.471 --> 42:27.035
When spiritual babies come to Redeemer, they look around and they want to scope out who else is here.

42:27.616 --> 42:29.618
And they say, these are my kind of people.

42:30.242 --> 42:32.224
These are the kind of people I want to be part of.

42:32.965 --> 42:34.026
Are they as smart as me?

42:34.086 --> 42:35.448
Are they as talented as me?

42:35.608 --> 42:36.529
Are they at my level?

42:37.510 --> 42:45.198
And it's true that you're spiritual babies because imagine that you can judge love and joy and patience and kindness and wisdom and humility by dress size.

42:46.880 --> 42:47.380
You can't.

42:48.762 --> 42:52.106
And it's going to be hard for some of you because a lot of you are very smart people.

42:52.486 --> 42:57.431
And natively, you're smarter than the people who are here who are spiritually much more mature than you.

42:57.451 --> 42:59.954
And you're going to have trouble with that, but you've got to see it.

43:01.090 --> 43:01.731
Can't you see it?

43:01.791 --> 43:05.817
Look, children are undiscriminating.

43:07.439 --> 43:13.307
You can fool them, and you will be easily fooled unless you learn the Bible.

43:14.269 --> 43:15.871
Children are exhibitionists.

43:17.814 --> 43:18.875
Children are exhibitionists.

43:18.895 --> 43:26.386
That means children really don't like, they get very bored unless the focus of attention is on them.

43:27.426 --> 43:30.069
You know, they'll be talking to you for a while, and then they'll say, well, enough about you.

43:30.109 --> 43:31.071
Don't you like my new shoes?

43:31.651 --> 43:32.973
I mean, that's the attitude of children.

43:33.073 --> 43:34.395
Children are exhibitionistic.

43:35.436 --> 43:38.580
Children always want you to talk about them and their needs.

43:40.102 --> 43:42.545
Spiritually, that happens too.

43:43.106 --> 43:50.895
A newborn child tends to be fairly selfish, kind of absorbed in their own needs, always wanting to talk about themselves.

43:54.079 --> 43:56.242
Children are also

43:56.578 --> 43:58.501
They tend to enjoy the spectacular.

43:58.521 --> 44:01.766
Have you ever noticed with children, you've got to exaggerate everything.

44:01.786 --> 44:05.511
You've got to say, it'll be a great day, won't it boys and girls?

44:05.831 --> 44:11.039
Because children have these very short attention spans and they can't see subtle nuances.

44:11.820 --> 44:14.925
And so spiritually, people very often want spectacular things.

44:14.945 --> 44:16.447
They want great preaching.

44:17.148 --> 44:18.510
They want a great church.

44:18.871 --> 44:19.732
They want miracles.

44:19.792 --> 44:22.275
They want to see dramatic things happening in their life.

44:22.296 --> 44:24.018
They don't like the routines.

44:24.290 --> 44:26.614
They don't like praying and reading their Bible every day.

44:26.654 --> 44:28.256
They don't like just learning the truth.

44:29.658 --> 44:31.902
Don't you see the spiritual babiness in you?

44:32.984 --> 44:35.768
You're unstable, you're undiscriminating, you're easily fooled.

44:36.409 --> 44:37.892
You tend to be exhibitionistic.

44:38.553 --> 44:42.298
You tend to like the spectacular and you don't like the grind.

44:43.560 --> 44:45.744
These are marks of the average Christian.

44:46.565 --> 44:49.790
These are the characteristics of the average church congregation.

44:50.572 --> 44:52.114
All I'm urging you to do

44:52.514 --> 44:55.618
is to humble yourself under them and say, on the one hand, encouraging.

44:55.638 --> 44:58.241
You used to say, yes, this is true of me, but I'm gonna outgrow it.

44:58.381 --> 44:59.503
See, that's the encouraging side.

44:59.763 --> 45:05.530
But on the other hand, you're gonna have to be willing to humble yourself under it and say, it doesn't matter my IQ.

45:05.570 --> 45:06.852
It doesn't matter my bank account.

45:06.872 --> 45:09.235
It doesn't matter how great I look.

45:10.316 --> 45:10.857
I'm a baby.

45:10.897 --> 45:13.180
I've got so much to learn.

45:13.821 --> 45:14.962
I've gotta submit.

45:15.458 --> 45:21.525
I can't be so busy and so important and so interested that I think, listen, let me tell you something.

45:21.545 --> 45:33.818
If you just show up here and come to worship services and you have not made yourself available for growth, for discipling, for study, for learning, you're just, you're almost like a homeless kid out there.

45:34.780 --> 45:36.021
Recognize who you are.

45:36.061 --> 45:38.063
Recognize your limitations.

45:40.145 --> 45:40.986
You know what the goal is?

45:41.046 --> 45:44.210
It's to stop being childish and become childlike.

45:45.474 --> 45:46.175
Look at Jesus.

45:46.275 --> 45:48.199
There you have the perfect child-like.

45:48.219 --> 45:52.346
It's good to be child-like, to be art-less like Jesus.

45:52.646 --> 45:56.693
There's no artificiality about children, and so there should be no artificiality about us.

45:57.314 --> 46:01.120
Our image shouldn't bother us.

46:01.561 --> 46:04.005
We shouldn't always be watching what other people think about us.

46:04.606 --> 46:06.329
You want child-likeness.

46:06.650 --> 46:07.251
Look at Jesus.

46:07.291 --> 46:08.132
He loved his father.

46:08.152 --> 46:09.434
He was dependent on his father.

46:09.975 --> 46:11.698
He didn't make a move without his father.

46:11.842 --> 46:12.463
childlike.

46:13.024 --> 46:18.352
He was completely artless and completely genuine and there was no artificiality, childlike.

46:18.852 --> 46:19.934
You want to be childlike.

46:21.456 --> 46:22.498
You don't want to get jaded.

46:22.518 --> 46:24.020
You want to get cynical.

46:24.461 --> 46:26.704
You want to be childlike but not childish.

46:27.105 --> 46:33.895
So look at Jesus because he was the most childlike and wise and mature person possible.

46:33.935 --> 46:34.776
That's what you're after.

46:34.836 --> 46:38.962
As newborn babes grow up

46:40.194 --> 46:41.155
Resolve tonight.

46:41.256 --> 46:41.897
I'm going to do it.

46:42.057 --> 46:42.738
Resolve tonight.

46:42.778 --> 46:43.899
I'm going to make that effort.

46:43.920 --> 46:45.642
I don't want to stay a baby for 10 years.

46:45.682 --> 46:46.263
It's possible.

46:47.104 --> 46:48.807
I don't want to stay a spiritual baby for 20 years.

46:49.147 --> 46:50.489
It's absolutely possible.

46:51.170 --> 46:53.253
Some of you are living proof that it's possible.

46:55.136 --> 46:57.399
Say tonight, I'm going to grow up.

46:57.920 --> 46:58.321
Let's pray.

46:58.341 --> 47:01.085
Thank you, Father, that it's possible to grow up.

47:01.486 --> 47:05.331
Thank you that so many of our sins and problems are the sins of children.

47:06.072 --> 47:06.954
We can outgrow them.

47:07.354 --> 47:09.938
Enable us to understand ourselves well enough.

47:10.242 --> 47:19.416
that we can come to you now humbly saying, oh Lord, show me how to crave the pure spiritual milk and to grow up into my salvation.

47:19.436 --> 47:25.344
Pray this in Jesus' name, amen.

47:26.506 --> 47:29.050
Thanks for joining us here on the Gospel and Life podcast.

47:29.530 --> 47:34.718
If you were encouraged by today's teaching, you can help others discover this podcast by rating and reviewing it.

47:35.139 --> 47:40.146
And to find more great gospel-centered content by Tim Keller, visit gospelandlife.com.

47:41.058 --> 47:42.902
Today's sermon was recorded in 1993.

47:43.103 --> 47:53.426
The sermons and talks you hear on the Gospel and Life podcast were recorded between 1989 and 2017, while Dr. Keller was senior pastor at Redeemer Presbyterian Church.

